condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Art. V 5.01 (a) | Description :A computer accounting software integrated into the MIS in the DCS would have beenmade operational, including with adequately trained staff, in a manner satisfactory to IDA | Due Date :01-Jul-2009

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.1 D | Description :The Recipient would have prepared, and furnished to IDA, for review and approval,an annual work program and budget each year by April 30 | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.IV B1b | Description :A contract, in form and substance satisfactory to IDA, between the Recipient anda Payment Service Provider, would have been signed. | Due Date :30-Jul-2010

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.IV B1b | Description :ToRs and RFP, in form and substance satisfactory to IDA, would have beenprepared and issued, for the purpose of selecting a consultant to carry out a program baseline and impact evaluation | Due Date:01-Sep-2010

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.V A. | Description :Experience with PCK would have been reviewed and agreement reached on futureapproach on payment mechanisms, no later than 12 months after effectiveness | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.V B. | Description :Impact Evaluation (for the 7 pilot districts) would have been reviewed and anaction plan, acceptable to IDA, would have been prepared by the Recipient, no later than 18 months after effectiveness | Due Date:30-Apr-2010

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.V C | Description :Periodic internal audit, in form satisfactory to IDA, would have been prepared,each 6 month period, from July to December and January to June each year | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Sch.2 Sec.V D. | Description :A midterm review of the project would have been carried out no later than 24months after effectiveness or later dated agreed with IDA | Due Date :12-Mar-2012
